== Useful snippets ==

In the following we provide some useful code snippets that are typically required in solutions.


==== Accessing a SPARQL Endpoint using HTTPS and Basic Authentication ====

The following snippet shows how a SPARQL Endpoint can be accessed using HTTPS and basic authentication. 

Note in particular that the following snippet trusts all SSL certificates.

<source>
// apache http client
import org.apache.commons.httpclient.protocol.Protocol;
import org.apache.commons.httpclient.protocol.ProtocolSocketFactory;

// open RDF API
import org.openrdf.query.QueryLanguage;
import org.openrdf.query.TupleQuery;
import org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryConnection;
import org.openrdf.repository.sparql.SPARQLRepository;

// located in fbase.jar - obtain it via the fluidOps client.zip
import com.fluidops.api.security.ssl.EasySSLProtocolSocketFactory;



Protocol easyhttps = new Protocol("https", (ProtocolSocketFactory)new EasySSLProtocolSocketFactory(), 8443);
Protocol.registerProtocol("https", easyhttps);

SPARQLRepository repo = new SPARQLRepository("https://localhost:8443/sparql");
repo.setUsernameAndPassword("admin", "iwb");
repo.initialize();

RepositoryConnection conn = repo.getConnection();

TupleQuery query = conn.prepareTupleQuery(QueryLanguage.SPARQL, "SELECT * WHERE { ?s ?p ?o } LIMIT 10");
...
</source>

==== Sending Email ====

Please make sure sending email is configured [[Setup:Email]].
Sending email can be done via the following API:

<source>
com.fluidops.iwb.util.MailControl.sendEmail("to@example.org", "subject", "text");
</source>
